Statisticians estimate the rapeseed crop at 1.305 million tons, which is more than last year.
The area under crops increased by 7.3 percent.
However, the yield per hectare will be 3.2 percent lower than last year.
This year's rapeseed crop will exceed the ten-year average by 13.3 percent, while the area sown is one-third larger than ten years ago.
In the last four years, poppy fields have also been increasing.
This year, farmers sowed it on 35,543 hectares.
Compared to 2008, when poppy was grown on a record 70,000 hectares in the Czech Republic, there are half of the fields.
Thanks to the expansion of the sown area, this year's poppy harvest will be richer.
It will rise by 2.5 percent compared to last year to 27,423 tonnes.
However, the yield per hectare will be 6.1 percent lower.
