They want to compete with carriers.
The idea to use the already planned routes for the transport of consignments is the work of television director Matěj Liška and the manager of the Prague music club Marek Greger.
With the idea, they breathed life into a trio of apps with different geographic reach.
We launched the domestic application Převezu in May.
At the moment, there are a thousand cities uploaded in it and we will expand the network.
In the Czech Republic, we want to learn it first before we focus more on foreign countries, says the forty-one-year-old manager in an interview for iDNES.cz.
How does the Prevezu app work and who can benefit from it?
Download it and register for free.
You can then enter the route and details of how big a package you can carry and how much you want for it.
Someone may be asking for a transport that day.
When the route and delivery time are suitable, it is paired and both receive a mutual notification.
At that moment, a chat will open, where the pair will arrange a handover.
How many people do you think would have to register to always find a courier for each package?
I do not know the ideal state, I can not estimate how many registered and how many trips are needed to ensure that the coverage is completely optimal and each offer is matched with the demand.
On the main roads it already works and it is logically easier than on the way between villages.
The more people, the greater the potential for speed and accuracy.
Meanwhile, people are also building trust and finding out that no one can run away with the package.
Have you not had to deal with such a case yet?
How many users does the service have after two months of launch?
Right now, we have about 5,000 to 6,000 people creating paths.
We consider this a success and we believe that more will be added.
Isn't there a risk that the sender will wait too long?
We hope to compete with large conglomerates just because we are able to deliver the same day and for a fraction of the price.
For a large company, you will pay several thousand for delivery within two hours.
Here you will pay a hundred or less, because it is a journey that someone is already taking.
Should traditional carriers be worried about a possible loss of customers in the future?
We hope so.
The market has a huge potential, huge multinational carriers are fed here, as well as retail chains, where everyone started to buy and gradually found out that the quality does not correspond to what they pay for.
No one wants to find a note in the mailbox with a message to pick up the shipment at a branch, no earlier than the day after 7 p.m.
By that time, I had needed the package for six hours and was waiting at home because it was important.
We want a better, faster and functional service that will not annoy anyone and will send a signal to the competition to try.
Marek Greger (41) and Matěj Liška (39).
Neither has ever worked in the field of information technology.
Marek Greger works as a manager of a music club, Matěj Liška as a television director.
In 2014, they started preparing the Shippansee LTD application, which uses already planned trips between world capitals, especially by plane, to transport packages.
In 2015, they commissioned a company that created applications for MALL.cz, Jobs.cz or ČSFD.
The programming took three quarters of a year and the application was launched on the market in March 2016.
They started developing the Převezu application in December last year and released it in May this year.
It is a local version of Shippansee adapted for the Czech market.
Profi has been developing the Messel and Moonstick applications since January this year and made it available to users at the end of July 2016.
The intention from the beginning was to make all these applications that will one day merge into one.
In the Czech Republic, they want to fine-tune the application and then, in cooperation with a strong investor, focus more on the global market.
The sharing economy has been a topic lately, and this is a service like AirBnB or Uber.
Aren't you worried about operating in an area about which no one can say much yet, where the boundary of sharing and where the shadow economy is?
It's the same, just a different product.
We know that if it succeeds and we go up with it, we will be another thorn in the side through the shadow economy.
But even if someone saves and someone earns, it is not the intention to circumvent tax offices and tax inspections.
Every user, on one side or the other, will be encouraged to tax their income if they make income out of it.
Why do you think the service has such great potential?
The sender saves and the transporter earns, respectively reduces the cost of the trip.
This is the powerful idea that unites interest on both sides.
In the age of social networks that divide people, we would like this one to bring people closer together.
Nice stories can be created, people are happy that they helped someone and they will talk about it.
Maybe someone will bring you forgotten glasses, keys or pills.
In my opinion, people have been missing a personal approach for a long time, we say about this application that it is a service of people to people.
So how do you guarantee that the courier will not flee with the package?
Each user of the application scans their ID card together with the registration and provides their bank details, payment or credit card.
These are the channels that give credibility to both service and man.
Couriers also collect stars based on senders' ratings.
We will also offer insurance, we are still fine-tuning the details.
In the event of loss or damage, the courier is liable for an uninsured shipment, but does not assume responsibility for the contents under criminal law if there is something illegal inside and he does not know about it.
If the police stop him and find a submachine gun or ten kilos of hashish in a sealed package in his suitcase, he falls on the criminal responsibility of the sender.
Is there a risk of misuse of sensitive data from the database?
If necessary, the registered are traceable by the administrative authority, which will be the only one able to see it, nor are we able to see them ourselves, the data is protected against misuse.
How much money will the courier get after successful delivery of the shipment?
The courier determines the price and gets the full amount he asks for.
The sender will be charged an extra few percent for providing contact.
This money is our profit, but it is only a few percent, because we want to push the volume.
Also, no one can accuse the courier of not delivering the parcel when he actually delivered it, the receipt and delivery is verified using QR codes.
Are there any limitations?
Whether in relation to the size or content of the package?
You can transport anything.
We have three sizes, small as a cube of butter, medium as a plate of eggs, and large as a bass of beers.
After that, there is no further restriction and if someone has space in the car, he can transport a refrigerator.
Plus, the sender has the option to take a picture of the package in the application, so the courier can see what is wanted from him.
You don't even have to pack the item if you don't really want to hide the content.
You put the forgotten sweatshirt in the courier's hand and that's it.
Who came up with the idea and how long did it take to launch the service?
A friend of mine got the idea more than two years ago, I didn't pay much attention to it at the time.
Then he showed me a demo app with transnational reach that mainly targets air passengers.
At that moment, I told him that I would not look for an investor, but I would like to become one myself and put my savings into it.
It took another year of development before we founded Shippansee LTD in London due to the greater credibility of the whole product.
But this is not the version you are focusing on now.
No, we focused our marketing on the Czech Republic, where we are trying to improve the application, because the whole thing had birth pains and there is still room for improvement and resolution.
We try to respond to customer feedback and we do not deal with the foreign market so much at the moment.
We know it's a long run, but we're not in a hurry, we want to create a really good product for people.
Shippansee LTD was the basic and most expensive application, the other two were upgrades in their own way.
I was born when we said that the domestic segment could be much more interesting and that we would at least learn it in the Czech Republic.
The third application of Mesíkem is local, for the city.
But it can send a package to the exact address and to the other side of the world.
It works for senders in the same way as Převezu, but the difference is that as a courier you can see shipments in the form of points on the map that are closest to you, thanks to the geolocator in your mobile.
We called the application for couriers who want to make a living from it Měsík Profi.
So someone can earn extra money by picking up packages around the city?
Exactly, the last application is downloaded in Prague by a taxi driver, a student, a mother on parental leave, someone who wants to make the most of the trip to work.
As everyone is fooling around with those Pokémon now, they can collect this just as well.
You see where the orders are around the city, you come to it, click and see when it has to be delivered and take the shipment away.
It's set up cheaper than competing services.
At the moment, we are still making a web interface that will be crucial for companies to send shipments, they will fill in the data on the web, so they will create points on the map.
We are then able to invoice them for the use of the service every month.
Are you now working full-time on the project?
It exhausts us, but we normally have it at work so that we can feed and develop the project.
We are not hiding a strong multinational investor, we are two guys, one of whom had a brilliant idea and the other jumped in with other suggestions and ideas.
Now we are looking for an investor strong enough to manage not the Czech market with us, but who should go with us to a global product and become another huge player on the market like AirBnB and Uber.
